I think Apple along with Adobe have realized that a certain amount of torrenting is good in the sense that people are actually learning how to use their products. How else would (thousands?) of teens get their start in the graphic design or production fields if they couldn't goof around and learn how the software works beforehand? 

Apple, and Adobe especially, receive the bulk of their software sales income from businesses buying in bulk. Kids who are designing little logos and making movies for fun don't pose any kind of threat to these massive companies, and there's not really much profit lost by letting a kid get their hands on an application for free that they wouldn't have purchased anyway.
